<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="619" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[683,1279,294,718]" pageId="21" pageNumber="619">
Although morphologically very close to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cretzschmar" baseAuthorityYear="1826" box="[688,833,409,443]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbilliscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="21" pageNumber="619" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="robustus">G. robustus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1878" box="[853,1045,409,443]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="21" pageNumber="619" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigricaudus">G. nigricaudus</taxonomicName>
was treated as a valid species by P. J. J. Bates in 1985 and 1988 and by I. Ya. Pavlinov and colleagues in 1990. Chromosomes were described by P. Colangelo and coworkers in 2005. A morphometric analysis by P. Colangelo and team in 2010 showed that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1878" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="21" pageNumber="619" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigricaudus">G. nigricaudus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cretzschmar" baseAuthorityYear="1826" box="[755,900,689,718]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbilliscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="21" pageNumber="619" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="robustus">G. robustus</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[987,1120,689,718]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbilliscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="21" pageNumber="619" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vicinus">G. vicinus</taxonomicName>
are clearly
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[73,1282,725,1784]" pageId="21" pageNumber="619">
distinct. Further molecular analysis by L. Granjon and colleagues in 2012 suggested that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1878" box="[146,341,773,798]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="21" pageNumber="619" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigricaudus">G. nigricaudus</taxonomicName>
belongs to an East African clade that includes also 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cretzschmar" baseAuthorityYear="1826" box="[1123,1271,773,798]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbilliscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="21" pageNumber="619" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="robustus">G. robustus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[77,215,805,839]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="21" pageNumber="619" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="phillipsi">G. phillipsi</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[297,428,805,839]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbilliscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="21" pageNumber="619" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vicinus">G. vicinus</taxonomicName>
. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="619" type="multiple">
<caption inLine="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="619" targetBox="[842,846,1759,1784]" targetPageId="21">
<paragraph blockId="21.[73,1282,725,1784]" box="[74,475,845,879]" pageId="21" pageNumber="619">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[74,475,845,879]" pageId="21" pageNumber="619">Subspecies and Distribution.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[73,1282,725,1784]" box="[78,882,883,917]" pageId="21" pageNumber="619">
<taxonomicName authority="Peters, 1878" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1878" box="[78,479,883,917]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbilliscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="21" pageNumber="619" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="nigricaudus" subSpecies="nigricaudus">G.n.nigricaudusPeters,1878—SKenyaandNETanzania.</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[73,1282,725,1784]" box="[78,1049,922,956]" pageId="21" pageNumber="619">
<taxonomicName authority="Dollman, 1911" authorityName="Dollman" authorityYear="1911" box="[78,448,922,956]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbilliscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="21" pageNumber="619" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="nigricaudus" subSpecies="nyama">G. n. nyama Dollman, 1911</taxonomicName>
— SW Ethiopia, SW Somalia, and N Kenya.
</paragraph>
</caption>
